Source: pg-mockable
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/bigsmoke/pg_mockable

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-mockable
Architecture: all
Provides: postgresql-pg-mockable
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Mock PostgreSQL functions for testing PGVERSION
  pg_mockable creates mockable wrapper functions in the mockable schema, so
  tests can replace calls to functions such as now() with deterministic values.
